Complete Story Recall

Modern DevOps relies heavily on Linux because it provides a stable, secure, and automation-friendly platform for running applications and infrastructure. Most DevOps tools, cloud platforms, and banking applications operate on Linux-based environments. Linux enables automation through scripting, simplifies monitoring and troubleshooting, and provides strong security controls. In banking environments such as Murex and Regulatory Reporting systems, Linux supports file processing, batch execution, monitoring, and operational stability. As organizations continue moving toward cloud platforms such as AWS, Linux remains a critical foundation for DevOps and cloud engineering.

