Glossary

Linux:
An operating system widely used in servers and enterprise environments.

Shell Script:
A sequence of Linux commands used to automate tasks.

Process:
A running application or program.

Log File:
A file that records application events and errors.

Cron Job:
A scheduled task in Linux.

Permission:
Controls who can read, write, or execute files and directories.

DevOps:
A culture and set of practices that combine Development and Operations teams to improve software delivery.
